de.must.markup
Interface Invokable

All Known Implementing Classes:
Back, ColumnDataList, CookbookAdministration, CookbookEnquiry, CookbookList, CookBookLogin, CookbookPresentation, DataList, DataPropertyAdministration, DataPropertyPresentation, DataTableAdministration, Dialog, Enquiry, LanguageChooserStd, LayoutChooserStd, List, LoginDialog, MainMenu, MustMenuBar, PasswordChangeDialog, PasswordChangeDialogStd, PropertyAdministration, PropertyPresentation, SimpleDataList, TypeAdministration, UserAdministration, UserEnquiry, UserList, UserPresentation
public interface Invokable

Invokables are components to be invoked by SessionStd and put in stack to control state maintaining and back functionality. Most of the invokables are dialogs to be nested in order to support complex administration. They show their face to the user via method #getTagSequence.

See Also:
SessionStd, Dialog

getInvokableInAdvance

java.lang.Class<? extends Invokable> getInvokableInAdvance()
Returns a Invokable class which is to be invoked before this Invokable can be shown. Sample: if a function needs a login, this login is to be done in advance.

a Invokable class which is to be invoked before this Invokable can be shown

isCancelable

boolean isCancelable()
Indicates whether the invokable accepts to be canceled. E.g. if properties are edited and jumping to another function is requested by using a toolbar option, this may be stopped here.

Returns:
true if the invokable accepts to be canceled

isSuitableDialog

boolean isSuitableDialog(GeneralizedRequest request)
Indicates whether the request fits to this dialog. Useful to stop the user to use any back functions of the browser.

Parameters:
request - the request to check
Returns:
true if the request fits to this dialog

fetchValuesFromRequest

void fetchValuesFromRequest(GeneralizedRequest request)
Causes the invokable to delegate this function to all embedded markupables to fetch their current value as edited by the user from the request.

Parameters:
request - the request from where the values are to be fetched
See Also:

process

setSubmitter

void setSubmitter(Invokable submitter)
Informs this invokable, from which previous invokable it is submitted. Technique to establish a bilateral communication between invokables.

Parameters:
submitter - the invokable that submitted this invokable

getSubmission

Submission getSubmission()
Informs the next invokable in stack about the submission details. E.g. a PropertyAdminstration may call this method to receive the primary key of the entry to be edited.

Returns:
the submission details

getStackMovement

int getStackMovement()
Returns the wished stack movement. E.g this if this invokable's work is done it return -1 to return to the previous invokable in the stack.
